  <summary>3/31/2003--Introduced.
Democracy Day Act of 2003 - Requires the Tuesday next after the first Monday in November in 2004 and in each even-number year thereafter (Election Day) to be treated in the same manner as November 11 (Veterans Day) for purposes of any laws relating to Federal employment. Urges private employers to give their employees that day off to enable them to vote.Directs the Comptroller General to conduct a study of the impact of such requirement on voter participation.</summary>
</bill>
